r_Nimoy_Laugh_Dragon_Con_2009.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ab/Shatner_Nimoy_Laugh_Dragon_Con_2009.jpg/266px-Shatner_Nimoy_Laugh_Dragon_Con_2009.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3888\" data-file-height=\"2592\" /></a></div>\n<p><i><b><a href=\"/wiki/Mind_Meld\" title=\"Mind Meld\">Mind Meld</a></b></i> is a 2001 American <a href=\"/wiki/Documentary_film\" title=\"Documentary film\">documentary film</a> in which actors <a href=\"/wiki/William_Shatner\" title=\"William Shatner\">William Shatner</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Leonard_Nimoy\" title=\"Leonard Nimoy\">Leonard Nimoy</a> <i>(pictured)</i> discuss the <i><a href=\"/wiki/Star_Trek\" title=\"Star Trek\">Star Trek</a></i> <a href=\"/wiki/Science_fiction\" title=\"Science fiction\">science-fiction</a> franchise and its effects on their lives. They talk about differences they had with <a href=\"/wiki/Gene_Roddenberry\" title=\"Gene Roddenberry\">Gene Roddenberry</a>, the creator of <i>Star Trek</i>, and about the strained relationships between Shatner and some of the other cast members. It was in this film that Nimoy first publicly revealed that he had struggled with <a href=\"/wiki/Alcoholism\" title=\"Alcoholism\">alcoholism</a> while he was acting in the <a href=\"/wiki/Star_Trek:_The_Original_Series\" title=\"Star Trek: The Original Series\">1960s <i>Star Trek</i> television series</a>. <i>Mind Meld</i> attracted some notoriety because of an unintended sound in one scene that became a popular subject of <a href=\"/wiki/Flatulence_humor\" title=\"Flatulence humor\">flatulence humor</a> among <a href=\"/wiki/Star_Trek_fandom\" title=\"Star Trek fandom\"><i>Star Trek</i> fans</a> and on <a href=\"/wiki/Morning_zoo\" title=\"Morning zoo\">morning zoo</a> radio programs. Shatner denied being the source of this sound in interviews. Scott Brown of <i><a href=\"/wiki/Entertainment_Weekly\" title=\"Entertainment Weekly\">Entertainment Weekly</a></i> said that the only people likely to watch the film were extreme <i>Star Trek</i> fans and people interested in hearing Shatner's supposed flatulence, while Laurence Lerman of <i>Video Business</i> praised the film for avoiding familiar territory and for dealing with alcoholism, career difficulties, and conflicts on the set of <i>Star Trek</i>. (<a href=\"/wiki/Mind_Meld\" title=\"Mind Meld\"><b>Full&#160;article...</b></a>)</p>\n<ul style=\"list-style:none; margin-left:0; text-align:right;\">\n<li>Recently featured:\n<div class=\"hlist inline\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/O_heilges_Geist-_und_Wasserbad,_BWV_165\" title=\"O heilges Geist- und Wasserbad, BWV 165\"><i>O heilges Geist- und Wasserbad</i>, BWV 165</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/George_Headley\" title=\"George Headley\">George Headley</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Speechless_(Michael_Jackson_song)\" title=\"Speechless (Michael Jackson song)\">\"Speechless\" (Michael Jackson song)</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=\"text-align: right;\" class=\"hlist noprint\" id=\"mp-tfa-footer\">\n<ul>\n<li><b><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Today%27s_featured_article/June_2015\" title=\"Wikipedia:Today's featured article/June 2015\">Archive</a></b></li>\n<li><b><a href=\"https://lists.wikimedia.org/mailman/listinfo/daily-article-l\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"mail:daily-article-l\">By email</a></b></li>\n<li><b><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Featured_articles\" title=\"Wikipedia:Featured articles\">More featured articles...</a></b></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"padding:2px;\">\n<h2 id=\"mp-dyk-h2\" style=\"margin:3px; background:#cef2e0; font-family:inherit; font-size:120%; font-weight:bold; border:1px solid #a3bfb1; text-align:left; color:#000; padding:0.2em 0.4em;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Did_you_know...\">Did you know...</span></h2>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"color:#000; padding:2px 5px 5px;\">\n<div id=\"mp-dyk\">\n<div><i>From Wikipedia's <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Recent_additions\" title=\"Wikipedia:Recent additions\">new and recently improved content</a>:</i></div>\n<div style=\"float:right; margin-left:0.5em;\" id=\"mp-dyk-img\">\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/File:Lamia_the_antic_gold_3.jpg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Gold exhibits at the Archaeological Museum of Lamia\"><img alt=\"Gold exhibits at the Archaeological Museum of Lamia\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/16/Lamia_the_antic_gold_3.jpg/100px-Lamia_the_antic_gold_3.jpg\" width=\"100\" height=\"75\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/16/Lamia_the_antic_gold_3.jpg/150px-Lamia_the_antic_gold_3.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/16/Lamia_the_antic_gold_3.jpg/200px-Lamia_the_antic_gold_3.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1600\" data-file-height=\"1200\" /></a></p>\n</div>\n<ul>\n<li>... that the <b><a href=\"/wiki/Archaeological_Museum_of_Lamia\" title=\"Archaeological Museum of Lamia\">Archaeological Museum of Lamia</a></b> exhibits <a href=\"/wiki/Bronze_Age\" title=\"Bronze Age\">Bronze Age</a> artifacts from the <a href=\"/wiki/Kynos\" title=\"Kynos\">Kynos</a> excavations, including gold ornaments <i>(pictured)</i>?</li>\n<li>... that journalist <b><a href=\"/wiki/Abby_Martin\" title=\"Abby Martin\">Abby Martin</a></b> condemned the <a href=\"/wiki/2014%E2%80%9315_Russian_military_intervention_in_Ukraine\" title=\"2014?\x80\x9315 Russian military intervention in Ukraine\">Russian military intervention in Ukraine</a> on the <a href=\"/wiki/RT_America\" title=\"RT America\">RT America</a> network?</li>\n<li>... that according to the <b><a href=\"/wiki/Embodied_bilingual_language\" title=\"Embodied bilingual language\">embodied bilingual language</a></b> theory, <a href=\"/wiki/Second_language\" title=\"Second language\">second language</a> words such as \"kick\" and \"run\" stimulate the parts of the motor cortex controlling leg movements?</li>\n<li>... that the <b><a href=\"/wiki/Askam_Borehole\" title=\"Askam Borehole\">Askam Borehole</a></b>, which was built by the Pennsylvania Department of Environmental Protection, discharges thousands of gallons of acid mine drainage into <a href=\"/wiki/Nanticoke_Creek\" title=\"Nanticoke Creek\">Nanticoke Creek</a> every minute?</li>\n<li>... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Robert_Grant_Haliburton\" title=\"Robert Grant Haliburton\">Robert Grant Haliburton</a></b> was instrumental in discovering the \"dwarf races\" of northern Africa and the Atlas region?</li>\n<li>... that the plot of the 2015 <a href=\"/wiki/Malayalam\" title=\"Malayalam\">Malayalam</a> film <i><b><a href=\"/wiki/Oru_Second_Class_Yathra\" title=\"Oru Second Class Yathra\">Oru Second Class Yathra</a></b></i> was found to begin well but end weakly?</li>\n<li>... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Daniel_Brustlein\" title=\"Daniel Brustlein\">Daniel Brustlein</a></b>, known as a cover artist for <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_New_Yorker\" title=\"The New Yorker\">The New Yorker</a></i>, received critical praise as a \"painter's painter\"?</li>\n<li>... that the wreck found off the coast of <b><a href=\"/wiki/Isla_San_Telmo\" title=\"Isla San Telmo\">Isla San Telmo</a></b> was established by <a href=\"/wiki/James_P._Delgado\" title=\"James P. Delgado\">James P. Delgado</a> as <a href=\"/wiki/Sub_Marine_Explorer\" title=\"Sub Marine Explorer\">one of the first submarines ever built</a>?</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=\"text-align:right;\" class=\"hlist noprint\" id=\"mp-dyk-footer\">\n<ul>\n<li><b><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Recent_additions\" title=\"Wikipedia:Recent additions\">Archive</a></b></li>\n<li><b><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Your_first_article\" title=\"Wikipedia:Your first article\">Start a new article</a></b></li>\n<li><b><a href=\"/wiki/Template_talk:Did_you_know\" title=\"Template talk:Did you know\">Nominate an article</a></b></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid transparent;\"></td>\n<td class=\"MainPageBG\" style=\"width:45%; border:1px solid #cedff2; background:#f5faff; vertical-align:top;\">\n<table id=\"mp-right\" style=\"width:100%; vertical-align:top; background:#f5faff;\">\n<tr>\n<td style=\"padding:2px;\">\n<h2 id=\"mp-itn-h2\" style=\"margin:3px; background:#cedff2; font-family:inherit; font-size:120%; font-weight:bold; border:1px solid #a3b0bf; text-align:left; color:#000; padding:0.2em 0.4em;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"In_the_news\">In the news</span></h2>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"color:#000; padding:2px 5px;\">\n<div id=\"mp-itn\">\n<div style=\"float:right;margin-left:0.5em;\" id=\"mp-itn-img\">\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/File:%D0%A1%D0%B0%D0%B9%D0%B3%D0%B0%D0%BA.jpg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Saiga antelope\"><img alt=\"Saiga antelope\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/22/%D0%A1%D0%B0%D0%B9%D0%B3%D0%B0%D0%BA.jpg/120px-%D0%A1%D0%B0%D0%B9%D0%B3%D0%B0%D0%BA.jpg\" width=\"120\" height=\"91\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/22/%D0%A1%D0%B0%D0%B9%D0%B3%D0%B0%D0%BA.jpg/180px-%D0%A1%D0%B0%D0%B9%D0%B3%D0%B0%D0%BA.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/22/%D0%A1%D0%B0%D0%B9%D0%B3%D0%B0%D0%BA.jpg/240px-%D0%A1%D0%B0%D0%B9%D0%B3%D0%B0%D0%BA.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"800\" data-file-height=\"609\" /></a></p>\n</div>\n<ul>\n<li>Almost half of the world's <b><a href=\"/wiki/Saiga_antelope\" title=\"Saiga antelope\">saiga antelopes</a></b> <i>(example pictured)</i>, a <a href=\"/wiki/Critically_endangered\" title=\"Critically endangered\">critically endangered</a> species, die in May from suspected <a href=\"/wiki/Pasteurellosis\" title=\"Pasteurellosis\">pasteurellosis</a>.</li>\n<li>Scientists describe a new <a href=\"/wiki/Hominini\" title=\"Hominini\">hominin</a> species, <i><b><a href=\"/wiki/Australopithecus_deyiremeda\" title=\"Australopithecus deyiremeda\">Australopithecus deyiremeda</a></b></i>.</li>\n<li>Following two separate criminal probes, Swiss police <b><a href=\"/wiki/2015_FIFA_corruption_case\" title=\"2015 FIFA corruption case\">arrest</a></b> seven <b><a href=\"/wiki/FIFA\" title=\"FIFA\">FIFA</a></b> officials and raid <a href=\"/wiki/FIFA_headquarters\" title=\"FIFA headquarters\">its headquarters</a>.</li>\n<li>Cable telecommunications company <b><a href=\"/wiki/Charter_Communications\" title=\"Charter Communications\">Charter</a></b> agrees to buy <b><a href=\"/wiki/Time_Warner_Cable\" title=\"Time Warner Cable\">Time Warner Cable</a></b> in a deal worth <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_dollar\" title=\"United States dollar\">US$</a>55.1&#160;billion.</li>\n<li><b><a href=\"/wiki/2015_Indian_heat_wave\" title=\"2015 Indian heat wave\">A heat wave</a></b> in India kills more than two thousand people.</li>\n<li>In motorsport, <a href=\"/wiki/Nico_Rosberg\" title=\"Nico Rosberg\">Nico Rosberg</a> wins the <b><a href=\"/wiki/2015_Monaco_Grand_Prix\" title=\"2015 Monaco Grand Prix\">Monaco Grand Prix</a></b>.</li>\n<li>Opposition candidate <a href=\"/wiki/Andrzej_Duda\" title=\"Andrzej Duda\">Andrzej Duda</a> is <b><a href=\"/wiki/Polish_presidential_election,_2015\" title=\"Polish presidential election, 2015\">elected</a></b> <a href=\"/wiki/President_of_Poland\" title=\"President of Poland\">President of Poland</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul style=\"list-style:none; margin-left:0;\">\n<li><b><a href=\"/wiki/Portal:Current_events\" title=\"Portal:Current events\">Ongoing events</a></b>:\n<div class=\"hlist inline\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/2015_Rohingya_refugee_crisis\" title=\"2015 Rohingya refugee crisis\">Rohingya refugee crisis</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Saudi_Arabian-led_intervention_in_Yemen\" title=\"Saudi Arabian-led intervention in Yemen\">Saudi Arabian-led intervention in Yemen</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li>\n<li><b><a href=\"/wiki/Deaths_in_2015\" title=\"Deaths in 2015\">Recent deaths</a></b></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"padding:2px;\">\n<h2 id=\"mp-otd-h2\" style=\"margin:3px; background:#cedff2; font-family:inherit; font-size:120%; font-weight:bold; border:1px solid #a3b0bf; text-align:left; color:#000; padding:0.2em 0.4em;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"On_this_day...\">On this day...</span></h2>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"color:#000; padding:2px 5px 5px;\">\n<div id=\"mp-otd\">\n<p><b><a href=\"/wiki/June_1\" title=\"June 1\">June 1</a></b>: <b><a href=\"/wiki/Children%27s_Day\" title=\"Children's Day\">International Children's Day</a></b>; <b><a href=\"/wiki/Parents%27_Day\" title=\"Parents' Day\">Global Day of Parents</a></b>; <b><a href=\"/wiki/Whit_Monday\" title=\"Whit Monday\">Day of the Holy Spirit</a></b> (Eastern Christianity, 2015); <b><a href=\"/wiki/Queen%27s_Official_Birthday\" title=\"Queen's Official Birthday\">Queen's Official Birthday</a></b> in New Zealand (2015); <b><a href=\"/wiki/Western_Australia_Day\" title=\"Western Australia Day\">Western Australia Day</a></b> (2015)</p>\n<div style=\"float:right;margin-left:0.5em;\" id=\"mp-otd-img\">\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/File:Prince_Imp%C3%A9rial,_1878,_Londres,_BNF_Gallica.jpg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Napolon Eugne Louis Jean Joseph Bonaparte\"><img alt=\"Napolon Eugne Louis Jean Joseph Bonaparte\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Prince_Imp%C3%A9rial%2C_1878%2C_Londres%2C_BNF_Gallica.jpg/63px-Prince_Imp%C3%A9rial%2C_1878%2C_Londres%2C_BNF_Gallica.jpg\" width=\"63\" height=\"100\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Prince_Imp%C3%A9rial%2C_1878%2C_Londres%2C_BNF_Gallica.jpg/94px-Prince_Imp%C3%A9rial%2C_1878%2C_Londres%2C_BNF_Gallica.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Prince_Imp%C3%A9rial%2C_1878%2C_Londres%2C_BNF_Gallica.jpg/126px-Prince_Imp%C3%A9rial%2C_1878%2C_Londres%2C_BNF_Gallica.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1522\" data-file-height=\"2419\" /></a></p>\n</div>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/1794\" title=\"1794\">1794</a> ?\x80\x93 The <b><a href=\"/wiki/Glorious_First_of_June\" title=\"Glorious First of June\">Glorious First of June</a></b>, the first and largest fleet action of the naval conflict between the Kingdom of Great Britain and the <a href=\"/wiki/First_French_Republic\" title=\"First French Republic\" class=\"mw-redirect\">First French Republic</a> during the <a href=\"/wiki/French_Revolutionary_Wars\" title=\"French Revolutionary Wars\">French Revolutionary Wars</a>, was fought.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/1879\" title=\"1879\">1879</a> ?\x80\x93 <b><a href=\"/wiki/Napol%C3%A9on,_Prince_Imperial\" title=\"Napolon, Prince Imperial\">Louis Napoleon</a></b> <i>(pictured)</i> was killed in action during the <a href=\"/wiki/Anglo-Zulu_War\" title=\"Anglo-Zulu War\">Anglo-Zulu War</a>, sending shock waves throughout Europe, as he was the last serious hope for the restoration of the <a href=\"/wiki/House_of_Bonaparte\" title=\"House of Bonaparte\">Bonapartes</a> to the French throne.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/1942\" title=\"1942\">1942</a> ?\x80\x93 <a href=\"/wiki/World_War_II\" title=\"World War II\">Second World War</a>: The crews of three Japanese <a href=\"/wiki/Type_A_Ko-hyoteki-class_submarine\" title=\"Type A Ko-hyoteki-class submarine\" class=\"mw-redirect\"><i>Ko-hyoteki</i> class submarines</a> scuttled and committed suicide after entering <a href=\"/wiki/Sydney_Harbour\" title=\"Sydney Harbour\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Sydney Harbour</a> and launching <b><a href=\"/wiki/Attack_on_Sydney_Harbour\" title=\"Attack on Sydney Harbour\">a failed attack</a></b>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/1974\" title=\"1974\">1974</a> ?\x80\x93 <b><a href=\"/wiki/Flixborough_disaster\" title=\"Flixborough disaster\">An explosion</a></b> at a <a href=\"/wiki/Chemical_plant\" title=\"Chemical plant\">chemical plant</a> close to the village of <a href=\"/wiki/Flixborough\" title=\"Flixborough\">Flixborough</a>, England, killed 28 people and seriously injured 36 others.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/2009\" title=\"2009\">2009</a> ?\x80\x93 En route from <a href=\"/wiki/Rio_de_Janeiro\" title=\"Rio de Janeiro\">Rio de Janeiro</a> to <a href=\"/wiki/Paris\" title=\"Paris\">Paris</a>, <b><a href=\"/wiki/Air_France_Flight_447\" title=\"Air France Flight 447\">Air France Flight 447</a></b> crashed into the Atlantic Ocean, killing all 228 aboard.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul style=\"list-style:none; margin-left:0;\">\n<li>More anniversaries:\n<div class=\"hlist inline nowraplinks\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/May_31\" title=\"May 31\">May 31</a></li>\n<li><b><a href=\"/wiki/June_1\" title=\"June 1\">June 1</a></b></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/June_2\" title=\"June 2\">June 2</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=\"text-align: right;\" class=\"hlist noprint\" id=\"mp-otd-footer\">\n<ul>\n<li><b><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Selected_anniversaries/June\" title=\"Wikipedia:Selected anniversaries/June\">Archive</a></b></li>\n<li><b><a href=\"https://lists.wikimedia.org/mailman/listinfo/daily-article-l\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"mail:daily-article-l\">By email</a></b></li>\n<li><b><a href=\"/wiki/List_of_historical_anniversaries\" title=\"List of historical anniversaries\">List of historical anniversaries</a></b></li>\n</ul>\n<div style=\"font-size:smaller;\">\n<ul>\n<li>Today is <span class=\"nowrap\">June 1, 2015</span> (<a href=\"/wiki/Coordinated_Universal_Time\" title=\"Coordinated Universal Time\">UTC</a>)</li>\n<li><span class=\"plainlinks\" id=\"otd-purgelink\"><span class=\"nowrap\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Main_Page&amp;action=purge\">Reload this page</a></span></span></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<table id=\"mp-middle\" style=\"width:100%; margin:4px 0 0 0; background:none; border-spacing: 0px;\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"MainPageBG\" style=\"width:100%; border:1px solid #f2cedd; background:#fff5fa; vertical-align:top; color:#000;\">\n<table id=\"mp-center\" style=\"width:100%; vertical-align:top; background:#fff5fa; color:#000;\">\n<tr>\n<td style=\"padding:2px;\">\n<h2 id=\"mp-tfl-h2\" style=\"margin:3px; background:#f2cedd; font-family:inherit; font-size:120%; font-weight:bold; border:1px solid #bfa3af; text-align:left; color:#000; padding:0.2em 0.4em\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"From_today.27s_featured_list\">From today's featured list</span></h2>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"color:#000;\">\n<div id=\"mp-tfl\" style=\"padding:2px 5px;\">\n<div id=\"mp-tfl-img\" style=\"float:right;margin:0.5em 0 0.4em 0.9em;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Chris_Carter_(July_2008).jpg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Chris Carter\"><img alt=\"A man with long white hair and a black suit, with a tie, is standing and smiling.\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bc/Chris_Carter_%28July_2008%29.jpg/100px-Chris_Carter_%28July_2008%29.jpg\" width=\"100\" height=\"125\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bc/Chris_Carter_%28July_2008%29.jpg/150px-Chris_Carter_%28July_2008%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bc/Chris_Carter_%28July_2008%29.jpg/199px-Chris_Carter_%28July_2008%29.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"442\" data-file-height=\"554\" /></a></div>\n<p><b><a href=\"/wiki/List_of_The_X-Files_episodes\" title=\"List of The X-Files episodes\">Two hundred two episodes</a></b> of the American <a href=\"/wiki/Science_fiction_on_television\" title=\"Science fiction on television\">science fiction</a>-<a href=\"/wiki/Supernatural_fiction\" title=\"Supernatural fiction\">supernatural</a> television series <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_X-Files\" title=\"The X-Files\">The X-Files</a></i> aired over nine seasons. The series originally ran on the <a href=\"/wiki/Fox_Broadcasting_Company\" title=\"Fox Broadcasting Company\">Fox</a> network from September 10, 1993 to May 19, 2002. <i>The X-Files</i> centers on <a href=\"/wiki/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\" title=\"Federal Bureau of Investigation\">FBI</a> special agents <a href=\"/wiki/Fox_Mulder\" title=\"Fox Mulder\">Fox Mulder</a> (<a href=\"/wiki/David_Duchovny\" title=\"David Duchovny\">David Duchovny</a>) and <a href=\"/wiki/Dana_Scully\" title=\"Dana Scully\">Dana Scully</a> (<a href=\"/wiki/Gillian_Anderson\" title=\"Gillian Anderson\">Gillian Anderson</a>), who work on cases linked to the paranormal, called <a href=\"/wiki/X-files_unit\" title=\"X-files unit\">X-Files</a>. Mulder is a believer in the <a href=\"/wiki/Paranormal\" title=\"Paranormal\">paranormal</a>, and the skeptical Scully is assigned to make scientific analyses of Mulder's discoveries which could ultimately be used to discredit his work. Throughout the series the two develop a close friendship. The show's premise originated with <a href=\"/wiki/Chris_Carter_(screenwriter)\" title=\"Chris Carter (screenwriter)\">Chris Carter</a> <i>(pictured)</i>, who served as an executive producer along with many others. Filming for seasons <a href=\"/wiki/The_X-Files_(season_1)\" title=\"The X-Files (season 1)\">one</a> to <a href=\"/wiki/The_X-Files_(season_5)\" title=\"The X-Files (season 5)\">five</a> took place primarily in <a href=\"/wiki/Vancouver\" title=\"Vancouver\">Vancouver</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/British_Columbia\" title=\"British Columbia\">British Columbia</a>, and for the remaining seasons in <a href=\"/wiki/Los_Angeles\" title=\"Los Angeles\">Los Angeles</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/California\" title=\"California\">California</a>. Episodes were broadcast on Fridays at 9:00&#160;p.m. <a href=\"/wiki/Eastern_Time_Zone\" title=\"Eastern Time Zone\">Eastern Standard Time</a> (EST) for the series's first three seasons; the remaining six seasons aired on Sundays at 9:00&#160;p.m. EST. (<b><a href=\"/wiki/List_of_The_X-Files_episodes\" title=\"List of The X-Files episodes\">Full&#160;list...</a></b>)</p>\n<ul style=\"list-style:none; margin-left:0; text-align:right;\">\n<li>Recently featured:\n<div class=\"hlist inline\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/List_of_1888%E2%80%9389_New_Zealand_Native_football_team_matches\" title=\"List of 1888?\x80\x9389 New Zealand Native football team matches\">1888?\x80\x9389 New Zealand Native football team matches</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Theodore_Sturgeon_Award\" title=\"Theodore Sturgeon Award\">Theodore Sturgeon Award</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/List_of_Knights_Grand_Cross_of_the_Royal_Victorian_Order_appointed_by_Edward_VII\" title=\"List of Knights Grand Cross of the Royal Victorian Order appointed by Edward VII\">Knights Grand Cross of the Royal Victorian Order appointed by Edward VII</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=\"text-align:right;\" class=\"hlist noprint\" id=\"mp-tfl-footer\">\n<ul>\n<li><b><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Today%27s_featured_list/June_2015\" title=\"Wikipedia:Today's featured list/June 2015\">Archive</a></b></li>\n<li><b><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Featured_lists\" title=\"Wikipedia:Featured lists\">More featured lists...</a></b></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<table id=\"mp-lower\" style=\"margin:4px 0 0 0; width:100%; background:none; border-spacing: 0px;\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"MainPageBG\" style=\"width:100%; border:1px solid #ddcef2; background:#faf5ff; vertical-align:top; color:#000;\">\n<table id=\"mp-bottom\" style=\"width:100%; vertical-align:top; background:#faf5ff; color:#000;\">\n<tr>\n<td style=\"padding:2px;\">\n<h2 id=\"mp-tfp-h2\" style=\"margin:3px; background:#ddcef2; font-family:inherit; font-size:120%; font-weight:bold; border:1px solid #afa3bf; text-align:left; color:#000; padding:0.2em 0.4em\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Today.27s_featured_picture\">Today's featured picture</span></h2>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"color:#000; padding:2px;\">\n<div id=\"mp-tfp\">\n<table style=\"margin:0 3px 3px; width:100%; text-align:left; background-color:transparent; border-collapse: collapse;\">\n<tr>\n<td style=\"padding:0 0.9em 0 0;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Locomotive_ChS8-075_2011_G1.jpg\" class=\"image\" title=\"ChS8\"><img alt=\"ChS8\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a9/Locomotive_ChS8-075_2011_G1.jpg/360px-Locomotive_ChS8-075_2011_G1.jpg\" width=\"360\" height=\"249\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a9/Locomotive_ChS8-075_2011_G1.jpg/540px-Locomotive_ChS8-075_2011_G1.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a9/Locomotive_ChS8-075_2011_G1.jpg/720px-Locomotive_ChS8-075_2011_G1.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"4700\" data-file-height=\"3250\" /></a></td>\n<td style=\"padding:0 6px 0 0\">\n<p>The <b><a href=\"/wiki/ChS8\" title=\"ChS8\">ChS8</a></b> is an <a href=\"/wiki/Electric_locomotive\" title=\"Electric locomotive\">electric</a> mainline passenger locomotive used in Russia and Ukraine. Built between 1983 and 1989, it was developed for pulling long passenger trains (28?\x80\x9332 carriages) at speeds of 100 kilometres per hour (60&#160;mph) or faster. Since 2010 Russia has switched to more energy-efficient designs, such as the <a href=\"/wiki/EP10\" title=\"EP10\">EP10</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/EP20\" title=\"EP20\">EP20</a>.</p>\n<p><small>Photograph: <a href=\"/wiki/User:George_Chernilevsky\" title=\"User:George Chernilevsky\">George Chernilevsky</a></small></p>\n<ul style=\"list-style:none; margin-left:0; text-align:right;\">\n<li>Recently featured:\n<div class=\"hlist inline\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Template:POTD/2015-05-31\" title=\"Template:POTD/2015-05-31\">Compound eyes</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Template:POTD/2015-05-30\" title=\"Template:POTD/2015-05-30\">Olmec heartland</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Template:POTD/2015-05-29\" title=\"Template:POTD/2015-05-29\">Impact sprinkler</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=\"text-align:right;\" class=\"hlist noprint\">\n<ul>\n<li><b><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Picture_of_the_day/June_2015\" title=\"Wikipedia:Picture of the day/June 2015\">Archive</a></b></li>\n<li><b><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Featured_pictures\" title=\"Wikipedia:Featured pictures\">More featured pictures...</a></b></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<div id=\"mp-other\" style=\"padding-top:4px; padding-bottom:2px;\">\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Other_areas_of_Wikipedia\">Other areas of Wikipedia</span></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><b><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Community_portal\" title=\"Wikipedia:Community portal\">Community portal</a></b> ?\x80\x93 Bulletin board, projects, resources and activities covering a wide range of Wikipedia areas.</li>\n<li><b><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Help_desk\" title=\"Wikipedia:Help desk\">Help desk</a></b> ?\x80\x93 Ask questions about using Wikipedia.</li>\n<li><b><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Local_Embassy\" title=\"Wikipedia:Local Embassy\">Local embassy</a></b> ?\x80\x93 For Wikipedia-related communication in languages other than English.</li>\n<li><b><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Reference_desk\" title=\"Wikipedia:Reference desk\">Reference desk</a></b> ?\x80\x93 Serving as virtual librarians, Wikipedia volunteers tackle your questions on a wide range of subjects.</li>\n<li><b><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:News\" title=\"Wikipedia:News\">Site news</a></b> ?\x80\x93 Announcements, updates, articles and press releases on Wikipedia and the Wikimedia Foundation.</li>\n<li><b><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Village_pump\" title=\"Wikipedia:Village pump\">Village pump</a></b> ?\x80\x93 For discussions about Wikipedia itself, including areas for technical issues and policies.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div id=\"mp-sister\">\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Wikipedia.27s_sister_projects\">Wikipedia's sister projects</span></h2>\n<p>Wikipedia is hosted by the <a href=\"/wiki/Wikimedia_Foundation\" title=\"Wikimedia Foundation\">Wikimedia Foundation</a>, a non-profit organization that also hosts a range of other <a href=\"//wikimediafoundation.org/wiki/Our_projects\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"wmf:Our projects\">projects</a>:</p>\n<table class=\"layout plainlinks\" style=\"width:100%; margin:auto; text-align:left; background:transparent;\">\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align:center; padding:4px;\"><a href=\"//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/\" t